Terblanche and Measey: The conservation value of freshwater habitats on frog communities of the Cape lowlands

John Measey & Naas Terblanche

2022-11-18

Supplementary Materials

submitted to PeerJ

The relationship between 50 sites sampled and their amphibian communities samplped from the Cape lowland fynbos in South Africa. Points and ellipses are coloured by wetland type: Temporary vlei purple, River edge green, Large dam brown, Small dam blue and Fynbos pool red (but with too few points to draw an ellipse). Ellipses demonstrate how site types are differentiated. The position and influence of species are shown with arrow lengths. (c) Points and ellipses are coloured by temporary (blue) or permanent (red) wetland types for NMDS1 and NMDS2, and (d) for NMDS2 and NMDS3. Species names are abbreviated to the first letters of genus and specific name (see Table 1).

Figure S1

Figure S1: A three dimensional NMDS showing the relationship between 50 sites sampled and their amphibian communities in the lowland fynbos. Ellipses are 95% confidence for different water body types. Note that temporary vleis (green) and fynbos pools (brown) and separated from large (purple) and small (yellow) dams, while both dams are not separated. Species names are abbreviated to the first letters of genus and specific name (see Table 1).
